Special provisions of Section 10 shall permit occupancies at building heights other than provided in Section 10

Individual occupancies shall be separated from adjacent occupancies in accordance with Table 10

Required separations shall be fire barriers constructed in accordance with Section 10 or horizontal assemblies constructed in accordance with Section 10 , or both , so as to completely separate adjacent occupancies

Incidental uses located within single occupancy or mixed occupancy buildings shall comply with the provisions of this section

Incidental uses are ancillary functions associated with a given occupancy that generally pose a greater level of risk to that occupancy and are limited to those uses listed in Table 10

Incidental uses within and serving a dwelling unit are not required to comply with this section

Incidental uses shall not be individually classified in accordance with Section 10

Incidental uses shall be included in the building occupancies within which they are located

Incidental uses shall not occupy more than 10 percent of the building area of the story in which they are located

Doors shall not have air transfer openings and shall not be undercut in excess of the clearance permitted in accordance with NFPA 80
